text:
Q: Apakah perlu bawa surat keterangan sehat dari UK untuk pulang ke Indonesia?
A: Mengingat tidak ada mekanisme surat keterangan sehat di UK, maka pada saat tiba di Indonesia akan mengisi kartu sehat dan menjalani pemeriksaan kesehatan.

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text:
Q: Apakah WNI dari UK tidak bisa pulang setelah tanggal 20 Maret?
A: Sebelum dan sesudah 20 Maret WNI dapat pulang ke Indonesia dengan ketentuan mengikuti pemeriksaan di point of entry di Indonesia. Jika ada gejala, masuk karantina Pemerintah. Tidak ada gejala, karantina mandiri.

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text:
Q: Apakah seluruh WNI diminta utk kembali ke tanah air?
A: Tidak. Himbauan utk segera kembali ke Indonesia adl utk WNI yg melakukan kunjungan singkat ke luar negeri. Bagi yg bekerja/studi silahkan melanjutkan aktivitas dg terus memperhatikan imbauan Pemerintah setempat & KBRI. https://t.co/cioZVeXVGP

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text:
51/Collaborative strategic outlook is very important to be brought forward for it will be the game changer for the current concerning world situation & it will boost higher
world economic growth. It has been #Indonesia’s commitment to be at the forefront of this. #PPTM2020

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 50/#Indonesia & @ASEAN aims to project through the #ASEANOutlook on the #Indo-#Pacific. The region is the present & future of Sustainable Global Growth. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 49/#Indonesia will foster alliances to continuously promote a fair & mutually beneficial paradigm & not a zero-sum game. The keyword is collaboration. It will create opportunities, develop new centres of economic growth & find solutions to the global challenges.  #PPTM2020

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 48/#Indonesia wishes to be at the front & part of the efforts to promote mutually beneficial collaboration in the world. Indonesia consistently builds a global coalition to strengthen the paradigm of cooperation & collaboration. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 47/In the next 5 years, economic diplomacy would be earnestly strengthened. @jokowi has given a mandate to the Vice Minister @Kemlu_RI to bolster Indonesia’s economic diplomacy. Concrete assignments will be entrusted to the Head of Missions. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 46/They are strengthening economic diplomacy, protection diplomacy, sovereignty & national identity diplomacy, #Indonesia’s leadership in the regional & global stage & the plus one is strengthening Indonesia’s diplomatic infrastructure. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 45/As for #Indonesia foreign policy priorities 2020 & directions for the next 5 years. Indonesia will conduct its diplomacy based on 4+1 priorities.#PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 44/Contingency plans; hotlines in #Indonesian Missions & Crisis Center at @Kemlu_RI  have been established to anticipate implications of the crisis towards Indonesian citizens. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 43/#2020 began with worrying situation in #Iran, #Iraq & its surroundings. #Indonesia hopes that all related parties can exercise self-restraint so as to avoid further escalation. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: DCM #KBRILondon menerima lukisan dari seniman Indonesia @tondihasibuan. Lukisan2 ini akan melengkapi karya seni dan budaya Indonesia di #KBRILondon . Terima kasih! https://t.co/TyLGSW4dgQ

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text:
42/#Indonesia & #Singapore has principally agreed on the flight information region realignment plan based on Indonesia’s territorial boundary post #UNCLOS1982. This will be continued by technical negotiations of the 2 countries & is
expected to be concluded in the near future.

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 41/#Indonesia & #Malaysia technical teams has principally agreed on the territorial sea boundary delimitation in #Sulawesi Sea. On land boundary demarcation, 4 out of 9 outstanding boundary problems has been settled with Malaysia. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 40/Indonesia & the Philippines concluded negotiations & deposited the EEZ Boundary Agreement to the @UN in Sep 2019. Both countries will immediately start & intensify negotiations on continental shelf boundary delimitation. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 39/The bilateral mechanism for citizen protection & consular coop were also strengthened. In 2019, consular consultations were conducted with #Australia, #India, #Iran, #EU, #Japan, & #Korea. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text:
38/#Indonesia has also been active in the global & regional norm setting process including: the adoption of @UN Resolution on “Violence Against Women Migrant Workers”,
Nov 2019; #Bali Process Policy Guide on Return & Reintegration. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 37/High profile #Indonesian cases that garnered public attention were also addressed: #SitiAisyah was released from murder charges; 40 #Indonesian citizens who were victims of mail order bride were successfully repatriated. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 36/..repatriating 17.607 #Indonesian citizens facing difficulties; & releasing 25 Indonesian citizens from capital punishment. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text:
35/#Indonesian citizen protection continued to be strengthen throughout 2019: handling 27.033 consular cases of Indonesian citizens abroad; recovering 197,71 billion rupiahs of Indonesian citizens/migrant workers financial
rights;..#PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 34/It is important for #Indonesia-#Malaysia-The #Philippines to strengthen preventive measures & avoid more victims. #Trilateral coop, security protection in & around #Sulu sea should be intensified. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text:
33/#Indonesia closed 2019 with the release of 2 #Indonesian hostages who were held in the Southern #Philippines. For the last 5 years, the Govt successfully released 45 Indonesian
hostages. Currently, 1 Indonesian citizen is still being held hostage. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 32/With such commitment, @ASEAN Leaders adopted the #ASEANOutlook on the #Indo-#Pacific as the guideline for ASEAN to establish engagement in the Indo-Pacific. This Outlook is inclusive & open for cooperation with all interested parties. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 31/@ASEAN must continue to come up with disruptive innovations, to step away from the comfort zone, & stay relevant in responding to current challenges. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 30/Power rivalry should be converted into coop. #Indonesia will continuously support @ASEAN in playing a central role in the promotion of peace, stability & prosperity in the #Indo-#Pacific region. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text:
29/ #Indonesia proposed the #Indo-#Pacific concept; hoping that stability, the habit of dialogue, collaboration, respect to
international law will always be upheld in the Indo-Pacific region. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text:
28/Throughout 2019, engagement with the #Pacific was consistently strengthened; building a new era of partnership with the Pacific countries, “Pacific Elevation”. #Indonesia too organised the Indonesia-South Pacific Forum in
#Jakarta & the Pacific Exposition in #Auckland.

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 27/#Indonesia stands ready to contribute in supplying basic needs for the people in #Rakhine State as well as build mutual trust in the society. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text:
26/#Indonesia continuously communicates with multiple parties: Govt of #Myanmar, #Bangladesh, #UN SecGen, Special Envoy of the UN SecGen, @Refugees, @UNmigration @ICRC & other related parties to help ensure progress on the
field. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 25/The Hospital is also hoped to fulfil the needs of the local communities for inclusive healthcare. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text:
24/Early Dec #2019, #Indonesia handed over a
hospital in Mrauk U, #Rakhine State, from the people of #Indonesia to the Govt of #Myanmar. It was built by people from various religions & ethnicity backgrounds & is hoped to bridge closer ties between communities in Rakhine State.

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text:
23/Communications with the displaced persons must continue; their voices must be heard, trust building should be consistently fostered so that voluntary, safe & dignified
repatriation can take place & conducive environment in #Rakhine State can be sustainable. #PPTM2020

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 22/#Indonesia appreciates the 2nd visit of the @ASEAN ASEAN team along with the Govt of #Myanmar & facilitated by the #Bangladesh authorities to #Cox’s Bazaar near the end of Dec 2019. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text:
21/#Indonesia continuously endeavors to be part of the solution to the #Rakhine State issue; ensuring that @ASEAN ASEAN could contribute & assuring that progress occurs
on the field. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text:
20/At the end of #2019, #Indonesia’s Foreign Policy, was concluded among others with a grant from the Govt of Indonesia to the Gov't of #Myanmar through the @ASEAN
Secretariat  to support the repatriation of displaced persons from #Cox’s Bazaar to #Rakhine State. #PPTM2020

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 19/Based on #Indonesia’s initiative, on 19 Dec 2019, the #UNGA adopted by consensus the resolution on creative economy & declared the year 2021 as the Int'l Year of Creative Economy for Sustainable Development. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 18/..along with several entities such as Africa Export-Import Bank, Standard Chartered Bank, Commerzbank & Development Bank of the Central African States. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

name: Indonesian Embassy-London

name: Indonesian Embassy-London

16/#Indonesia’s economic coop priority with #Africa is embodied, among others through the “Indonesia-Africa Infrastructure Dialogue" as a follow up to the Indonesia-Africa
Forum in 2018. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 15/..initiated negotiation with #Fiji, the 1st negotiation with the South #Pacific region; negotiations with the European Union is still ongoing. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 14/FTA negotiation with #Chile also concluded; first trade agreement in #Latin #America & the #Caribbean region; #RCEP negotiation concluded after 28 rounds since 2013; signed MoC with #EAEU; .. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 13/In 2019: #CEPA negotiations with #Australia & #EFTA were concluded; #PTA negotiation with #Mozambique were also concluded. #Indonesia’s first PTA in #Africa; .. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 12/With this mindset, #Indonesia continues to bolster its #economic #diplomacy. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 11/#Indonesia consistently broadens its economic cooperation based on the principle of mutual benefit. Trade & investment coop should be mutually beneficial, fair & not a zero-sum game. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 10/#2019 was also marked by growing protectionism, slower economic growth & global trade down to its lowest point since the 2009 global financial crisis. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

name: Indonesian Embassy-London

name: Indonesian Embassy-London

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 5/Investing in women also means investing in peace. During the past year, #Indonesia has made large investments on women, peace & security issues. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 4/#Indonesia started 2019 with its membership in the #UNSC. It will continue until the end of 2020. “Investing in peace” is the grand spirit that underlies Indonesia’s work as non-permanent member of UNSC. #PPTM2020 #IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #Indonesia4PeaceAndSecurity

text: Is there more to gain? To answer this question, Mr. Natalegawa believed that Indonesia should create a reciprocal and mutually beneficial outlook that creates a comfort level and trust within ASEAN rather than what benefits Indonesia more

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: Mr. Natalegawa continued by saying rather than seeing ASEAN as the hindrance for Indonesia's global ambition, Indonesia wishes to bring ASEAN to the global stage hence the notion of 'Indonesia as the regional power with global interest.'

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: Our second speaker, Mr. Marty Natalegawa, said that Indonesia and ASEAN influences each other, positively and negatively, and it is up to the leaders to balance this dynamic

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: Mr. Wanandi also argued that the involvement of the second and third tracks, such as NGOs, in the discussion in ASEAN is necessary

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: Our first speaker, Mr. Jusuf Wanandi, highlighted the importance of ASEAN as a regional institution to ensure the peaceful coexistence between great powers in the region as the only way to move forward

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: Good morning! ASEAN@CSIS Seminar Series Inaugural Seminar titled "Indonesia in ASEAN: Is there More to Gain?" has started https://t.co/Glwx1o67sc

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: Bambang is the foremost expert on forest fires in Indonesia. His expertise allows him to pinpoint the cause of these incredibly destructive fires and he has testified in hundreds of court cases and faced harassment and threats doing so. #MaddoxPrize

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: The winner of the 2019 #MaddoxPrize is Bambang Hero Saharjo https://t.co/kneOOGfnvM https://t.co/vnssEm14yX

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: Some of his colleagues testify on behalf of palm oil companies, and say he is stupid for standing against them. Despite this, and the continued pressure, he will not stop. He says it is his moral responsibility.

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: He uses his research and expertise to provide clarity to the jury, when the opposition have often tried to confuse them with bunk science. He receives harassment and threats when he testifies, and was sued for $33 million by a palm oil company over a technicality.

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: The winner of the 2019 #MaddoxPrize Prof Bambang Hero Saharjo exemplifies all the qualities of the prize and more. As the foremost expert of forest fires in Indonesia, he testifies against private companies who are responsible for illegal forest fires in Indonesia. https://t.co/AXl0dWmER5

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text:
We have now reached the end of our event Thank you for following our Twitter thread on "Indonesia, ASEAN, and the Indo-Pacific: Strategic Necessities or Norm-Setting Exercise".

Today's event was also recorded on our YouTube channel and posted on our Instagram stories,

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text:
A final question asked by @dinopattidjalal, how does @jokowi as a foreign policy decision-maker compare with himself five years ago?

Ambassador @DrRizalSukma reiterates foreign policy begins at home, and foreign policy should benefit national priorities.

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text:
The third and final round of questions conferred:
- what Indonesia does to uphold ASEAN unity
- importance of norms building into practical & actionable policy
- the BRI; 
- ASEAN to have its own regional court to uphold rules-based principles?
- ASEAN as umbrella organisation

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: The second round of questions addressed ASEAN's inclusiveness and connectivity; Pakistan, Bangladesh, and Sri Lanka being part of the South East Asian strategy; and denial of legitimacy and using East Asia Summit as a platform.

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: @DrRizalSukma @pjvermonte @KBRILondon The first round of questions discussed the South China Sea and the importance of enforcement of rules through power: physical, military, etc., as well as IORA's involvement and @DrRizalSukma's problem with Indo-Pacific being seen with a geographical mindset.

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: We have now begun the Q&A session with Ambassador @DrRizalSukma https://t.co/pS20VewlKF

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: For the Ambassador's closing statement, @DrRizalSukma remarks Indonesia's commitment reflect our responsibilities and commitment for the region; do not change ASEAN for the location of extra-regional rivalries.

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text:
@DrRizalSukma The five key issues to be addressed: 
1. Articulating clarity on ASEAN position on Indo-Pacific Outlook
2. Develop regional discussions
3. ASEAN should speak with one voice to strengthen ASEAN centrality
4. ASEAN to strengthen maritime security
5. Soft balancing strategy

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: @DrRizalSukma There are five actions that need to be taken by Indonesia: (1) reclaim identity, (2) secure, utilise, & reserve our maritime resources, (3) improve maritime infrastructure, (4) work with our partners on our position in the GMF, (5) develop & strengthen our defence capabilities

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: In regards to the ASEAN Indo-Pacific Outlook, @DrRizalSukma observes two important points: (1) it is imperative to continue implementing the GMF agenda, (2) Continue driving common policy and strategy discussion within ASEAN to develop the outlook

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: @DrRizalSukma @pjvermonte Ambassador @DrRizalSukma acknowledges different challenges require different response. ASEAN can no longer sit and watch extra-regional powers actively shift power in the region. Indonesia hopes the ASEAN Indo-Pacific Outlook will address the shifting challenges in the region.

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: @DrRizalSukma @pjvermonte Ambassador @DrRizalSukma remarks that this is his first public speech. The ambassador expresses his gratitude towards CSIS for having created impact to his personal hope, a place where the ambassador learned as a scholar that he should never hesitate to speak his mind.

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text:
@DrRizalSukma Dr. @pjvermonte introduced and welcomed @DrRizalSukma to the floor. 

Dr Sukma was previously the Executive Director of CSIS Indonesia.

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text:
Good morning!

Today's CSIS Lecture Series on Regional Dynamics:

"Indonesia, ASEAN, and the Indo-Pacific: Strategic Necessities or Norm-Setting Exercise?" 

with @DrRizalSukma, Indonesian Ambassador to the UK, Rep. of Ireland & IMO

has commenced

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text:
7. There are two imperatives for Indonesia.
 First, to continue implementing the GMF agenda comprehensively.
 Second, to continue driving the discussion within ASEAN on a common policy and strategy to navigate the Indo-Pacific. #indopacific #AOIP

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 6. As the #AOIP originates from Indonesia, it’s logical to expect that Indonesia would continue to take the lead in ensuring that the AOIP does what it is meant to do. #indopacific #AOIP

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text: 5. Amb @DrRizalSukma further argued that it’s imperative to move from hope and expectation to policy and strategy. However, the burden and responsibility of doing so rests first and foremost with Indonesia. #indopacific

name: Indonesian Embassy-London
text:
4. Indonesia hopes and expects AOIP to address strategic challenges in the region, and give impetus for greater regional cooperation
In strategic terms, it hopes the AOIP could serve as a platform through which rivalries among great powers can be mitigated and conflict prevented.
